<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2297] java.sql.Time objects are incorrectly formatted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2297</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Log4j2 incorrectly formats instance objects of &lt;b&gt;java.sql.Time&lt;/b&gt;. Consider following case -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;final Time time = Time.valueOf(&quot;12:00:00&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
 logger.info(&quot;Time : {}&quot;, time);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
 Now, the expected output is &lt;b&gt;Time : 12:00:00&lt;/b&gt; but instead it is logged as &lt;font color=&quot;#333333&quot;&gt;Time : &lt;/font&gt;&lt;b&gt;1970-01-01T12:00:00.000+0530&lt;/b&gt;. Since &lt;b&gt;java.sql.Time&lt;/b&gt; has no date component, it is wrong to format it this way.&lt;br/&gt;
 &#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13149148">LOG4J2-2297</key>
